Taints and Tolerance
Taints & Tolerations (Compact Notes)
🔷 Basic Concept
Taint → applied on node → blocks pods
Toleration → applied on pod → allows pods
Default: pods cannot go to tainted nodes

👉 Memory:

Taint = Node says NO
Toleration = Pod says OK
🔷 Add / Remove Taint
kubectl taint nodes node1 key=value:NoSchedule
kubectl taint nodes node1 key=value:NoSchedule-
🔷 Effects
NoSchedule → new pods blocked
PreferNoSchedule → try to avoid
NoExecute → evict running pods
🔷 Basic Pod YAML
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: nginx
spec:
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx
  tolerations:
  - key: "env"
    operator: "Equal"
    value: "dev"
    effect: "NoSchedule"
🔷 Operators (ONLY 2)
Equal (default) → key + value must match
Exists → only key must match (value ignored)
🔷 Equal Example

Node:

kubectl taint nodes node1 env=dev:NoSchedule

Pod:

tolerations:
- key: "env"
  operator: "Equal"
  value: "dev"
  effect: "NoSchedule"

✔️ Allowed
❌ If value ≠ dev → blocked

🔷 Exists Example
tolerations:
- key: "env"
  operator: "Exists"
  effect: "NoSchedule"

✔️ Allowed even if value different

🔷 Your Case

Node:

kubectl taint nodes node1 env=dev:NoSchedule

Pod:

tolerations:
- key: "env"
  operator: "Exists"
  effect: "NoSchedule"

✔️ Scheduled (value ignored)

🔷 Matching Rules
Key must match
Effect must match
Equal → value must match
Exists → value ignored
🔷 Defaults / Edge Cases
No operator → Equal
Exists → no value needed
No effect → matches all effects
Empty key + Exists → matches all taints
🔷 NoExecute with Time
tolerations:
- key: "env"
  operator: "Equal"
  value: "dev"
  effect: "NoExecute"
  tolerationSeconds: 60

→ stays 60 sec → evicted

🔷 Multiple Taints Logic
Kubernetes filters taints
If any NoSchedule not tolerated → blocked
If any NoExecute → evicted
PreferNoSchedule → try to avoid
🔷 Important Notes
Toleration ≠ guarantee scheduling
Scheduler still checks CPU/memory
🔷 Real Use Case
kubectl taint nodes gpu-node type=gpu:NoSchedule
tolerations:
- key: "type"
  operator: "Equal"
  value: "gpu"
  effect: "NoSchedule"
🔷 Difference (Important)
Tolerations → Equal, Exists
Node Affinity → In, NotIn, Exists, DoesNotExist
